                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170416-87-off447 t18170416-87-crimeloc450"></join>. The prisoner was my <rs id="t18170416-87-deflabel451" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170416-87-defend689 t18170416-87-deflabel451"></join>. Having frequently missed silver, I marked some about one o'clock on the 20th of March, and put it into a bason in the bar. She went out about five o'clock to collect the pots, and I missed three 3s. tokens, and a half-crown. I went after her, and brought her back, and found 1l. 3s. 6d., in silver, in her pockets-my three 3s. pieces, and half-crown, which I had marked, were among them. I might have lost more. She said it was her own money.</p>
               <p>
            
